            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>tomato paste</strong>,<strong> dried oregano, white wine vinegar</strong>,<strong> chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chipotle paste</strong> and <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lemon[s] </strong>in a bowl</p><p>Add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then mix to combine – this is your <strong>peri peri sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1621865859662-x200.jpg",
